        <type>s32</type>
        <definition>s32 XAsu_KeyWrapUnwrapValidateInputParams</definition>
        <argsstring>(const XAsu_KeyWrapParams *KwpunwpParamsPtr, u8 OperationType)</argsstring>
        <name>XAsu_KeyWrapUnwrapValidateInputParams</name>
        <param>
          <type>const <ref refid="struct_x_asu___key_wrap_params" kindref="compound">XAsu_KeyWrapParams</ref> *</type>
          <declname>KwpunwpParamsPtr</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u8</type>
          <declname>OperationType</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function validates input parameters for key wrap and unwrap. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>KwpunwpParamsPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to <ref refid="struct_x_asu___key_wrap_params" kindref="compound">XAsu_KeyWrapParams</ref> structure that holds the input parameters for Key wrap and unwrap </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>OperationType</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Indicates whether the operation is AES/RSA key wrap/unwrap or AES key wrap/unwrap</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS, if input validation is successful.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE, if input validation fails. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Validate that the addresses of all input and output buffers are non-zero.</para><para>Validate that the length of all input and output sizes are non-zero.</para><para>Validate AES key size.</para><para>Validate that exactly one of KeyCompAddr or RsaKeyId is provided.</para><para>Validate SHA Mode and SHAType.</para><para>Validate RSA key size. </para>        </inbodydescription>
